    <p class="mb-4">
      Austria offers one of Europe's best value propositions for international students: affordable tuition (€726/semester for non-EU), excellent ÖGK health insurance (~€70/month), and life in Vienna—consistently ranked the world's most livable city. Total annual costs of €12,000-18,000 are very competitive.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The ÖGK student self-insurance is genuinely excellent—comprehensive coverage at a fraction of what you'd pay in Switzerland or for private insurance. Most students should choose this option without hesitation. The post-graduation Rot-Weiß-Rot Karte pathway makes Austria attractive for those wanting to stay in Europe.
    </p>

